, THE TOTAL GROSS UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS, EXCLUDING RELATED INTEREST AND PENALTIES, WERE

$506 MILLION

,

$264 MILLION

OF WHICH WOULD AFFECT THE COMPANY'S EFFECTIVE TAX RATE IF RECOGNIZED IN FUTURE PERIODS.

THE COMPANY RECOGNIZES INTEREST AND PENALTIES RELATED TO INCOME TAX MATTERS IN INCOME TAX EXPENSE. THE LIABILITY FOR PAYMENT OF INTEREST AND PENALTIES INCREASED

